es\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Roddick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Roddick\"}, {\"begin\": 289, \"end\": 303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.6610102522998721, \"rank\": 0.5015939147115611, \"text\": \"Serb\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 37-year-old beat Carlos Alcaraz in straight sets to finally claim the prize he'd wanted above all other, having achieved everything else in tennis throughout his glittering career.\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 382, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Djokovic is a marmite figure in sport, with not everybody a huge fan of the Serb.But Roddick has a message for the veteran's critics, insisting they do not deserve to watch tennis if they are a fan on social media 'ripping on' the icon.Novak Djokovic critics have been blasted by Andy Roddick after the tennis star recently won gold at the Paris Olympics|REUTERS\\\"If you are a fan that is on Twitter ripping on Novak, then you do not deserve to watch tennis,\\\" he said.Djokovic won gold at the Olympics just weeks after he'd been thumped by Alcaraz in the final of Wimbledon.Roddick has been blown away by the Serb's latest achievement, with the American saying Djokovic's gold ends the GOAT (greatest of all time) argument once and for all.\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 547, \"end\": 555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999989606759244, \"rank\": 1.039325221323428e-06, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999989606759244, \"rank\": 1.039325221323428e-06, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 827, \"end\": 839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Roddick\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andy Roddick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Roddick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Roddick\"}, {\"begin\": 887, \"end\": 901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 938, \"end\": 945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.644804357759505e-16, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}, {\"begin\": 1086, \"end\": 1093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.646931637158448e-16, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 1155, \"end\": 1159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.6610102522998721, \"rank\": 0.5015939147115611, \"text\": \"Serb\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}, {\"begin\": 1191, \"end\": 1199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9472073770075727, \"rank\": 0.051015958793377364, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1207, \"end\": 1215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999989606759244, \"rank\": 1.039325221323428e-06, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Words will fail me when trying to express the respect that I have for Novak, obviously for the totality of his career,\\\" he said.JUST IN:Noah Lyles refuses to apologise and admits to deliberately hiding Covid diagnosis from rivals at the Olympics\\\"Both of these things are true: he's been physically compromised all year, and he said during the offseason last year that he would take a gold medal over any tournament in 2024, and I believe him.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1423, \"end\": 1433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think a lot of people say that because they feel like they should; Novak means it because that's the only hole in his resume.\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The only thing you can argue for someone else over Novak is an Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He continued: \\\"He knows that going out, you have been physically compromised all year, you have not won a tournament, you have not beaten a top 10 player all year, you had knee surgery on June 6th, and you won Olympic gold singles against the current best player on earth on August 4th.READ MORE:Mike Tyson 'not well enough to train' as boxing fans fume over new Jake Paul fight announcement\\\"You feel like there was a weight around this, you know?\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2304, \"end\": 2313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jake Paul\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's won Wimbledon seven times, not saying the Wimbledon final is not the pinnacle of our sport.\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I felt like this meant more, just based on feelings.\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think Wimbledon helped, and I think he was healthy going in, and he was pretty honest about it.\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2551, \"end\": 2560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_Wimbledon_Championships\", \"score\": 0.6230557776772512, \"rank\": 0.3968162261393032, \"text\": \"Wimbledon\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q13219666\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_Wimbledon_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_Wimbledon_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He said like, 'I feel better here than I did at Wimbledon by far.\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'LATEST SPORTS NEWS:British Olympic medallist shuts down Good Morning Britain host over misinformationTravis Kelce 'desperately trying to console Taylor Swift' with pop star 'shaken' after terror plot foiledEmma Raducanu makes 'impatience' confession as tennis star prepares for US Open - 'Biggest downfalls'Novak Djokovic beat Carlos Alcaraz in straight sets to win his first gold medal at the Olympics|REUTERS\\\"He knew that his best chance at a medal, and we said this in the weird quasi-Olympic show from last week, he did not mess around with doubles, he did not stay in the village.\", \"from\": 2706, \"to\": 3292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2726, \"end\": 2733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.8886651463025639, \"rank\": 0.12400322749570059, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {\"begin\": 2985, \"end\": 2992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\", \"score\": 0.935861658826044, \"rank\": 0.027464247762228403, \"text\": \"US Open\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\"}, {\"begin\": 3020, \"end\": 3028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999989606759244, \"rank\": 1.039325221323428e-06, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 3034, \"end\": 3048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He had a singular focus: 'This is what I have to do.\", \"from\": 3292, \"to\": 3345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'\\\"While Djokovic has ended his wait for a gold medal, he will not be retiring any time soon.Speaking after his win over Alcaraz, the 24-time Grand Slam winner said he was targeting the Los Angeles Olympics in 2028 as he looks to add to his remarkable legacy.Novak Djokovic was jubilant after beating Carlos Alcaraz to win gold at the Olympics|REUTERS\\\"I still want to play in Los Angeles,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3345, \"to\": 3742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3353, \"end\": 3361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999989606759244, \"rank\": 1.039325221323428e-06, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 3465, \"end\": 3472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.646931637158448e-16, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 3530, \"end\": 3550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9992529612194856, \"rank\": 0.0007475972648842535, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3609, \"end\": 3617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"s